<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/8218½</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mrs. <persName type="from">Woodrow Wilson</persName> to
                            the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-02">December 2, 1919</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>The President feels it will do no harm to delay the departure until the 9th
                        but advises that all of the Commission leave at that date and that this be
                        made final.</p>
                    <closer><signed>E B W[<hi rend="smallcaps">ilson</hi>]</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>